    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - Description -
        FENDER EXTENSIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <para>Fender extensions are an integral part of the fender system on the 8500 series vehicles. The fender
            extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. This protects the lower front of the
            cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the step cleaner (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900609">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900609" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900609.png" type="png" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" resolution="200"/>
